<h3>OS Installation Process: Step-by-Step</h3>
<div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    
    <h4>Common Installation Steps (All OSes)</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #fff; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0;">
        <ol style="line-height: 1.8;">
            <li><b>Boot from USB:</b> Press boot menu key (F12, F10, ESC, DEL) during startup</li>
            <li><b>Select Language/Region:</b> Choose your language, keyboard layout, timezone</li>
            <li><b>Installation Type:</b> 
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Upgrade:</b> Keep files and settings (Windows)</li>
                    <li><b>Custom/Clean:</b> Fresh install (recommended)</li>
                    <li><b>Dual Boot:</b> Install alongside existing OS</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>Partitioning:</b> Most critical step - we'll cover this in detail tomorrow</li>
            <li><b>User Account Setup:</b> Create username, password, computer name</li>
            <li><b>Installation Progress:</b> Files copy, features install (20-60 minutes)</li>
            <li><b>Initial Configuration:</b> Privacy settings, updates, optional features</li>
            <li><b>First Boot:</b> Welcome screen, final setup, driver installation</li>
            <li><b>Post-Installation:</b> Install drivers, updates, essential software</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <h4>Windows-Specific Installation Notes</h4>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
        <div>
            <h5>Windows 10/11 Installation</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Product Key:</b> Can skip and activate later</li>
                <li><b>Windows Edition:</b> Home vs Pro (Pro recommended)</li>
                <li><b>Drive 0:</b> Usually your main drive</li>
                <li><b>Delete partitions:</b> Removes existing OS and data</li>
                <li><b>Secure Boot:</b> Must be disabled for some Linux dual-boot</li>
                <li><b>TPM 2.0:</b> Required for Windows 11</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
            <h5>Common Windows Issues</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><b>"No drives found":</b> Need storage drivers (F6 during install)</li>
                <li><b>Boot failure:</b> Check Secure Boot and Legacy/UEFI settings</li>
                <li><b>Activation issues:</b> Digital license tied to Microsoft account</li>
                <li><b>Driver issues:</b> Download LAN/WiFi drivers beforehand</li>
                <li><b>Partition errors:</b> Use diskpart clean command if stuck</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h4>Linux-Specific Installation Notes</h4>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
        <div>
            <h5>Ubuntu Installation</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Try vs Install:</b> "Try Ubuntu" tests hardware first</li>
                <li><b>Minimal vs Normal:</b> Minimal has fewer preinstalled apps</li>
                <li><b>Download updates:</b> Check during install for latest packages</li>
                <li><b>Third-party software:</b> Includes codecs, drivers (recommended)</li>
                <li><b>Installation type:</b>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Erase disk and install Ubuntu</li>
                        <li>Install alongside Windows (dual boot)</li>
                        <li>Something else (manual partitioning)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
            <h5>Common Linux Issues</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><b>No boot menu:</b> May need to repair GRUB bootloader</li>
                <li><b>WiFi not working:</b> May need proprietary drivers</li>
                <li><b>NVIDIA issues:</b> Use open-source "nouveau" or proprietary drivers</li>
                <li><b>UEFI issues:</b> May need to disable Secure Boot</li>
                <li><b>Partition mounting:</b> Understand / (root), /home, swap partitions</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>Hands-On Activity: Virtual Installation Lab</h3>
<div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
