    <h4>File System Architecture Concepts</h4>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
        <div>
            <h5>Key Concepts Explained</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Journaling:</b> Keeps log of changes before writing to disk (NTFS, ext4)
                    <ul>
                        <li>Prevents corruption during power loss</li>
                        <li>Slower writes, faster recovery</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><b>Cluster/Block Size:</b> Minimum storage unit (4KB typical)
                    <ul>
                        <li>Small files waste space (slack space)</li>
                        <li>Larger clusters = faster but more wasted space</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><b>Metadata:</b> Data about data (permissions, timestamps, location)</li>
                <li><b>Fragmentation:</b> Files split across non-contiguous clusters
                    <ul>
                        <li>Slows down read/write operations</li>
                        <li>Modern file systems reduce this</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
            <h5>File System Components</h5>
            <pre style="background-color: #f1f1f1; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
