    <p><b>Part 3: Scripting Best Practices Checklist</b></p>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
EVALUATE YOUR SCRIPTS AGAINST THESE BEST PRACTICES:

[ ] 1. SHEBANG PRESENT:
    Linux: #!/bin/bash or #!/usr/bin/env bash
    Windows: @echo off at minimum

[ ] 2. ERROR HANDLING:
    Check for command success: if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
    Validate arguments
    Handle missing files/directories

[ ] 3. INPUT VALIDATION:
    Check number of arguments
    Validate argument values
    Provide helpful error messages

[ ] 4. COMMENTS:
    Header comment with purpose/usage
    Section comments for complex logic
    Inline comments for non-obvious code

[ ] 5. VARIABLE NAMES:
    Descriptive names (not a, b, c)
    UPPER_CASE for environment/constants
    lower_case for local variables

[ ] 6. QUOTING:
    Quote variables: "$variable"
    Quote paths with spaces
    Use single quotes for literals

[ ] 7. EXIT CODES:
    Return 0 on success
    Return non-zero on failure
    Consistent error codes

[ ] 8. PORTABILITY:
    Avoid shell-specific features when possible
    Use / instead of \ for paths
    Handle different OS environments

[ ] 9. SECURITY:
    No hardcoded passwords
    Validate user input
    Use appropriate permissions

[ ] 10. TESTING:
     Test with valid inputs
     Test with invalid inputs
     Test edge cases

