            "4-2": {
                icon: "fa-pizza-slice",
                title: "Digital Pizza Delivery & Packet Structure",
                html: `<h1>Week 4, Day 2: Digital Pizza Delivery & Packet Structure</h1>
        <p>Today we explore packet-based communication through the "Digital Pizza Delivery" analogy and understand packet structure in detail.</p>

        <div class="analogy-box">
            <b>Analogy: Digital Pizza Delivery ğŸ•</b><br />

            Data Packet: Pizza box<br />
            IP Address: Restaurant & Customer addresses<br />
            TCP/UDP: Delivery method (car vs scooter)<br />
            Router: Crossroads/directions<br />
            Switch: Neighborhood delivery hub<br />
            Packet Loss: Dropped pizza slice<br />
            Reassembly: Putting pizza together at destination
        </div>

        <h3>Understanding Data Packets</h3>
        <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
            <h4>ğŸ“¦ What is a Packet?</h4>

            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; border: 2px solid #4A90E2;">
                    <h5>ğŸ¢ The "Digital Pizza" Analogy</h5>
                    <p><b>Large Data = Whole Pizza</b></p>
                    <ol style="padding-left: 20px;">
                        <li><b>Cut into slices:</b> Data divided into packets</li>
                        <li><b>Each slice in box:</b> Packet with headers</li>
                        <li><b>Address labels:</b> Source/destination IP</li>
                        <li><b>Delivery instructions:</b> Protocol info</li>
                        <li><b>Different delivery routes:</b> Routing paths</li>
                        <li><b>Reassembly at destination:</b> Putting slices together</li>
                        <li><b>Missing slice?</b> Request retransmission</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>

                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; border: 2px solid #e74c3c;">
                    <h5>ğŸ“Š Packet Structure Components</h5>
                    <table style="width: 100%;">
                        <tr>
