                icon: "fa-map-marker-alt",
                title: "IP Addressing & IPv4 Basics",
                html: `<h1>Week 5, Day 1: IP Addressing & IPv4 Basics</h1>
    <p>Today we dive deep into IP addressing, understanding how devices are identified on networks and mastering IPv4 fundamentals.</p>

    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: The Digital Postal System ğŸ </b><br />

        IP Address: House address (123 Main St)<br />
        Subnet Mask: Street boundaries (Main St vs Oak St)<br />
        Gateway: Local post office<br />
        DNS: Phone book (name to address lookup)<br />
        DHCP: Address assignment office<br />
        Public IP: Mailing address visible to world<br />
        Private IP: Internal room numbers
    </div>

    <h3>Understanding IP Addresses</h3>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
        <h4>ğŸŒ What is an IP Address?</h4>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <div>
                <h5>The Digital Identifier</h5>
                <p>An IP (Internet Protocol) address is a <b>unique numerical label</b> assigned to each device connected to a computer network that uses the Internet Protocol for communication.</p>

                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin-top: 10px; border: 2px solid #3498db;">
                    <h6>IPv4 Address Format:</h6>
                    <div style="text-align: center; padding: 15px; background: #e3f2fd; border-radius: 5px;">
                        <div style="font-size: 2em; font-family: monospace; font-weight: bold;">
                            192 . 168 . 1 . 10
                        </div>
                        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 10px; margin-top: 10px;">
                            <div style="padding: 5px; background: #bbdefb;">Octet 1</div>
                            <div style="padding: 5px; background: #90caf9;">Octet 2</div>
                            <div style="padding: 5px; background: #64b5f6;">Octet 3</div>
                            <div style="padding: 5px; background: #42a5f5;">Octet 4</div>
                        </div>
                        <div style="margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.9em;">
                            Each octet: 0-255 (8 bits = 1 byte)<br>
                            Total: 32 bits = 4 bytes
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin-top: 15px;">
                        <h6>Binary Representation:</h6>
                        <table style="width: 100%; font-family: monospace;">
                            <tr>
                                <td style="padding: 5px; background: #bbdefb;">192</td>
                                <td style="padding: 5px; background: #90caf9;">168</td>
                                <td style="padding: 5px; background: #64b5f6;">1</td>
                                <td style="padding: 5px; background: #42a5f5;">10</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="padding: 5px;">11000000</td>
                                <td style="padding: 5px;">10101000</td>
                                <td style="padding: 5px;">00000001</td>
                                <td style="padding: 5px;">00001010</td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h5>Quick Reference</h5>
                <table style="width: 100%; background: white; border-radius: 5px; padding: 10px;">
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Total IPv4 Addresses</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">4.3 Billion</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Address Size</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">32 bits</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Format</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Dotted Decimal</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Octet Range</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">0-255</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Example</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">192.168.1.1</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Subnet Mask</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">255.255.255.0</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>

                <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #fff3cd; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>ğŸ¯ Important Notes:</h6>
                    <ul style="font-size: 0.8em;">
                        <li>0.0.0.0 = Default route</li>
                        <li>127.0.0.1 = Loopback</li>
                        <li>255.255.255.255 = Broadcast</li>
                        <li>169.254.x.x = APIPA (auto IP)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Public vs Private IP Addresses</h3>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
        <div style="background: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <h4>ğŸ  Private IP Addresses</h4>
            <p>Used <b>within</b> private networks (LANs), not routable on the Internet.</p>

            <table style="width: 100%; margin-top: 10px;">
                <tr style="background: #27ae60; color: white;">
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Class</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Range</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Subnet Mask</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Hosts</th>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">A</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">10.0.0.0 - 10.255.255.255</td>
