            </table>

            <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #d4edda; border-radius: 5px;">
                <h5>Common Private IPs:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Home Routers:</b> 192.168.1.1 or 192.168.0.1</li>
                    <li><b>Default Gateway:</b> Usually .1 or .254</li>
                    <li><b>DHCP Range:</b> 192.168.1.100-200 (typical)</li>
                    <li><b>Static Devices:</b> Printers, servers (.10, .20, etc.)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="background: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <h4>ğŸŒ Public IP Addresses</h4>
            <p>Globally unique addresses routable on the <b>Internet</b>.</p>

            <table style="width: 100%; margin-top: 10px;">
                <tr style="background: #e74c3c; color: white;">
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Class</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Range</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Purpose</th>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">A</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">1.0.0.0 - 126.255.255.255</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Large organizations</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">B</td>
