                    <td style="padding: 8px;">C</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">192-223</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">24</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">8</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">2,097,152</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">254</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">255.255.255.0</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #fff3cd; border-radius: 5px;">
                <p><b>âš ï¸ Note:</b> Classful addressing is mostly obsolete! We now use CIDR (Classless Inter-Domain Routing), but understanding classes helps with subnetting.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Binary Math for IP Addressing</h3>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <h4>ğŸ”¢ Essential Binary Concepts</h4>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <div>
                <h5>Binary to Decimal Conversion</h5>
                <table style="width: 100%; font-family: monospace; text-align: center;">
                    <tr style="background: #4A90E2; color: white;">
                        <th style="padding: 8px;">Bit Position</th>
                        <th style="padding: 8px;">Value</th>
                        <th style="padding: 8px;">Binary</th>
                        <th style="padding: 8px;">Decimal</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2â·</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">128</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">128</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2â¶</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">64</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">64</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2âµ</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">32</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">32</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2â´</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">16</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">16</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2Â³</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">8</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">8</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2Â²</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">4</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">4</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2Â¹</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">2â°</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #4A90E2; color: white;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Total</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">255</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">11111111</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">255</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>

                <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: white; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>Example: Convert 192 to Binary</h6>
                    <p>192 = 128 + 64 = 11000000</p>
                    <p>Check: 128Ã—1 + 64Ã—1 + 32Ã—0 + 16Ã—0 + 8Ã—0 + 4Ã—0 + 2Ã—0 + 1Ã—0 = 192</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h5>IP Address in Binary</h5>
                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>IP: 192.168.1.10 / Subnet: 255.255.255.0</h6>

                    <table style="width: 100%; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.9em;">
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 5px;"><b>Component</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 5px;"><b>Decimal</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 5px;"><b>Binary</b></td>
