            "5-2": {
                icon: "fa-exchange-alt",
                title: "DHCP vs Static IP & Subnetting Basics",
                html: `<h1>Week 5, Day 2: DHCP vs Static IP & Subnetting Basics</h1>
    <p>Today we explore automatic vs manual IP assignment and begin our journey into subnetting - the art of dividing networks efficiently.</p>

    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: The Hotel Room Assignment System ğŸ¨</b><br />

        DHCP: Automatic check-in (get room key at front desk)<br />
        Static IP: Pre-booked suite (specific room reserved)<br />
        IP Range: All available rooms in hotel<br />
        Subnet: Different hotel floors/wings<br />
        Lease Time: How long you keep the room<br />
        Reservation: DHCP reservation (specific room for VIP)
    </div>

    <h3>DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol)</h3>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
        <h4>ğŸ”„ How DHCP Works - The DORA Process</h4>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <div>
                <h5>The Four-Step Dance: D-O-R-A</h5>

                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; border: 2px solid #3498db;">
                    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 10px; text-align: center;">
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #bbdefb; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <b>Step 1: Discover</b>
                            <div style="font-size: 0.8em;">"Is there a DHCP server?"</div>
                        </div>
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #90caf9; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <b>Step 2: Offer</b>
                            <div style="font-size: 0.8em;">"Here's an IP for you"</div>
                        </div>
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #64b5f6; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <b>Step 3: Request</b>
                            <div style="font-size: 0.8em;">"I'll take that IP"</div>
                        </div>
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #42a5f5; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <b>Step 4: Acknowledge</b>
                            <div style="font-size: 0.8em;">"IP assigned, here's config"</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; background: #e3f2fd; border-radius: 5px;">
                        <h6>Detailed DORA Process:</h6>
                        <pre style="background: white; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; font-family: monospace;">
Client                  DHCP Server
  |---- Discover ------>| (Broadcast: 255.255.255.255:67)
  |                     | "Any DHCP server out there?"
  |<---- Offer ---------| (Unicast to client)
  |                     | "Here's IP 192.168.1.100"
  |---- Request ------>| (Broadcast)
  |                     | "I accept 192.168.1.100"
  |<---- ACK ----------| (Unicast to client)
  |                     | "Confirmed! Lease: 24 hours"
                    </pre>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                    <h5>DHCP Renewal Process</h5>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                        <p>When lease reaches <b>50%</b> of TTL (Time To Live):</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>Client sends DHCPREQUEST to current server</li>
                            <li>Server responds with DHCPACK (extends lease)</li>
                            <li>If no response, try again at 87.5% of lease</li>
                            <li>If still no response, start new DORA process</li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h5>DHCP Configuration</h5>
                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>Typical DHCP Scope:</h6>
                    <table style="width: 100%;">
                        <tr>
