    <h3>Introduction to Subnetting</h3>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <div>
                <h4>ğŸ¯ Why Subnetting?</h4>

                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h5>The Problem:</h5>
                    <p>You have a single network with 254 hosts (192.168.1.0/24). Problems:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>Broadcast Traffic:</b> Every device sees all broadcasts</li>
                        <li><b>Security:</b> All devices are in same broadcast domain</li>
                        <li><b>Performance:</b> Too many devices competing for bandwidth</li>
                        <li><b>Organization:</b> No logical grouping of devices</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5 style="margin-top: 15px;">The Solution - Subnetting:</h5>
                    <p>Divide 192.168.1.0/24 into smaller networks:</p>
                    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 10px; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;">
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #bbdefb; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <b>Subnet 1</b><br>192.168.1.0/26<br>62 hosts
                        </div>
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #90caf9; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <b>Subnet 2</b><br>192.168.1.64/26<br>62 hosts
                        </div>
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #64b5f6; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <b>Subnet 3</b><br>192.168.1.128/26<br>62 hosts
                        </div>
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #42a5f5; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <b>Subnet 4</b><br>192.168.1.192/26<br>62 hosts
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h4>ğŸ“ˆ Subnetting Benefits</h4>
                <table style="width: 100%; background: white; border-radius: 5px; padding: 10px;">
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">ğŸ¯</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Reduced Broadcast</b></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">ğŸ”’</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Improved Security</b></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">âš¡</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Better Performance</b></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">ğŸ¢</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Logical Organization</b></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">ğŸŒ</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Geographic Separation</b></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">ğŸ’°</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Efficient IP Use</b></td>
                    </tr>
                </table>

                <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #fff3cd; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h5>Key Terms:</h5>
                    <ul style="font-size: 0.8em;">
                        <li><b>Subnet Mask:</b> Defines network vs host portions</li>
                        <li><b>Network Address:</b> First address in subnet</li>
                        <li><b>Broadcast Address:</b> Last address in subnet</li>
                        <li><b>Host Range:</b> Usable addresses</li>
                        <li><b>CIDR:</b> Slash notation (/24, /26, etc.)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>The Magic Number Method</h3>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
        <h4>ğŸ”¢ Step-by-Step Subnetting Method</h4>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <div>
                <h5>Example: Create 4 Subnets from 192.168.1.0/24</h5>

                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>Step 1: Determine Requirements</h6>
                    <p>We need 4 subnets. How many bits to borrow?</p>
                    <p>Formula: 2^n â‰¥ required subnets</p>
                    <p>2^2 = 4 âœ“ (need 2 bits)</p>

                    <h6 style="margin-top: 15px;">Step 2: New Subnet Mask</h6>
                    <p>Original: /24 = 255.255.255.0</p>
                    <p>Add 2 bits: /24 + 2 = /26</p>
                    <p>New mask: 255.255.255.192</p>

                    <h6 style="margin-top: 15px;">Step 3: Magic Number</h6>
                    <p>256 - last octet of mask</p>
                    <p>256 - 192 = 64 â† Magic Number!</p>
                    <p>This is our subnet increment</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h5>Step 4: Subnet Ranges</h5>
                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <table style="width: 100%; font-size: 0.9em;">
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <th style="padding: 8px;">Subnet</th>
                            <th style="padding: 8px;">Network</th>
                            <th style="padding: 8px;">Range</th>
                            <th style="padding: 8px;">Broadcast</th>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">1</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">192.168.1.0</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">.1 - .62</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">192.168.1.63</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">2</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">192.168.1.64</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">.65 - .126</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">192.168.1.127</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">3</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">192.168.1.128</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">.129 - .190</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">192.168.1.191</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">4</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">192.168.1.192</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">.193 - .254</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">192.168.1.255</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>

                    <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #e8f5e8; border-radius: 5px;">
                        <h6>Quick Check:</h6>
                        <p>Each subnet has 64 total addresses:</p>
                        <p>â€¢ Network address (1)</p>
                        <p>â€¢ Usable hosts (62)</p>
                        <p>â€¢ Broadcast address (1)</p>
                        <p>Total: 64 addresses per subnet</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; background: white; border-radius: 5px;">
            <h5>ğŸ“Š Subnetting Cheat Sheet</h5>
            <table style="width: 100%;">
                <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">CIDR</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Mask</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Subnets</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Hosts/Subnet</th>
                    <th style="padding: 8px;">Magic #</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">/25</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">255.255.255.128</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">2</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">126</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">128</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">/26</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">255.255.255.192</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">4</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">62</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">64</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">/27</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">255.255.255.224</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">8</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">30</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">32</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">/28</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">255.255.255.240</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">16</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">14</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">16</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">/29</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">255.255.255.248</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">32</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">6</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">8</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">/30</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">255.255.255.252</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">64</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">2</td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">4</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Practical Subnetting Examples</h3>
    <div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <div>
