            "5-4": {
                icon: "fa-question-circle",
                title: "Troubleshooting IP Issues & Quiz",
                html: `<h1>Week 5, Day 4: Troubleshooting IP Issues & Quiz</h1>
    <p>Today we consolidate our IP addressing knowledge through troubleshooting exercises and a comprehensive quiz to test your understanding.</p>

    <div class="analogy-box">
        <b>Analogy: The Network Detective ğŸ•µï¸â€â™‚ï¸</b><br />

        Symptoms: Crime scene evidence<br />
        Tools: Detective's toolkit (commands)<br />
        Process: Systematic investigation<br />
        Clues: Error messages, logs<br />
        Solution: Case solved<br />
        Prevention: Crime prevention strategies
    </div>

    <h3>Troubleshooting Methodology</h3>
    <div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
        <h4>ğŸ” The Systematic Approach</h4>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <div>
                <h5>OSI Model Troubleshooting (Bottom-Up)</h5>

                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; border: 2px solid #3498db;">
                    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(7, 1fr); gap: 5px; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                        <div style="padding: 5px; background: #bbdefb; border-radius: 3px;">Layer 7</div>
                        <div style="padding: 5px; background: #90caf9; border-radius: 3px;">Layer 6</div>
                        <div style="padding: 5px; background: #64b5f6; border-radius: 3px;">Layer 5</div>
                        <div style="padding: 5px; background: #42a5f5; border-radius: 3px;">Layer 4</div>
                        <div style="padding: 5px; background: #2196f3; border-radius: 3px;">Layer 3</div>
                        <div style="padding: 5px; background: #1e88e5; border-radius: 3px;">Layer 2</div>
                        <div style="padding: 5px; background: #1976d2; border-radius: 3px;">Layer 1</div>
                    </div>

                    <ol>
                        <li><b>Layer 1 - Physical:</b> Check cables, lights, power</li>
                        <li><b>Layer 2 - Data Link:</b> Check MAC addresses, switches</li>
                        <li><b>Layer 3 - Network:</b> Check IP addresses, routing</li>
                        <li><b>Layer 4 - Transport:</b> Check ports, firewalls</li>
                        <li><b>Layers 5-7 - Upper:</b> Check applications, services</li>
                    </ol>

                    <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #e3f2fd; border-radius: 5px;">
                        <h6>Divide and Conquer:</h6>
                        <p>Start at Layer 1 and work up, or start in the middle (Layer 3) and work in both directions.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                    <h5>Troubleshooting Mindset</h5>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                        <table style="width: 100%;">
                            <tr>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; width: 30%;"><b>1. Gather Information</b></td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px;">What works? What doesn't? When did it stop?</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                                <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>2. Reproduce the Problem</b></td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px;">Can you make it fail consistently?</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>3. Isolate the Cause</b></td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px;">Network? Device? Application?</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                                <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>4. Implement Solution</b></td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px;">Fix the root cause, not symptoms</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>5. Verify Resolution</b></td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px;">Test thoroughly, monitor</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                                <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>6. Document</b></td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px;">What happened? What fixed it?</td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h5>Quick Reference Cards</h5>
