            "6-1": {
                icon: "fa-route",
                title: "Routers vs Switches & DNS Intro",
                html: `<h1>Week 6, Day 1: Routers vs Switches & DNS Introduction</h1>
<p>Today we explore the core networking devices that make the Internet work: routers and switches, and begin our journey into DNS - the Internet's phone book.</p>

<div class="analogy-box">
    <b>Analogy: The Transportation Network ğŸšš</b><br/>
    
    Switch: Local delivery truck (within neighborhood)<br/>
    Router: Highway interchange (between cities)<br/>
    MAC Address: House address (permanent, physical)<br/>
    IP Address: City/street address (logical, can change)<br/>
    ARP: Asking "Who lives at this house?"<br/>
    DNS: Phone book (name to address lookup)<br/>
    Gateway: City limits sign
</div>

<h3>Switches: The Traffic Directors</h3>
<div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
    <h4>ğŸ”€ Layer 2 Switching</h4>
    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
        <div>
            <h5>How Switches Work</h5>
            
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; border: 2px solid #3498db;">
                <h6>The Learning Process:</h6>
                <div style="text-align: center; padding: 20px;">
                    <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #bbdefb; border-radius: 5px;">Computer A<br>MAC: AA:AA:AA:AA:AA:AA</div>
                    <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px;">â†’ Port 1 â†’</div>
                    <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 15px; background: #e3f2fd; border-radius: 5px; border: 2px solid #2196f3;">
                        <b>SWITCH</b><br>
                        MAC Table:<br>
                        Port 1: AA:AA:AA:AA:AA:AA
                    </div>
                    <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px;">â† Port 2 â†</div>
                    <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #90caf9; border-radius: 5px;">Computer B<br>MAC: BB:BB:BB:BB:BB:BB</div>
                </div>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                    <h6>Switch Operations:</h6>
                    <table style="width: 100%;">
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 8px; width: 30%;"><b>Learning:</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Records MAC addresses and port mappings</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Forwarding:</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Sends frames only to destination port</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Filtering:</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Prevents frames from going to wrong ports</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Flooding:</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Sends to all ports if destination unknown</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <h5>Types of Switches</h5>
                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 15px;">
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #e8f5e8; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <h6>Unmanaged Switches</h6>
                            <ul style="font-size: 0.9em;">
                                <li><b>Plug and play</b></li>
                                <li>No configuration needed</li>
                                <li>Basic home/office use</li>
                                <li>Fixed functionality</li>
                                <li>Example: Netgear GS105</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div style="padding: 10px; background: #fff3cd; border-radius: 5px;">
                            <h6>Managed Switches</h6>
                            <ul style="font-size: 0.9em;">
                                <li><b>Full configuration</b></li>
                                <li>VLANs, QoS, security</li>
                                <li>Enterprise networks</li>
                                <li>CLI or web interface</li>
                                <li>Example: Cisco Catalyst</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div>
            <h5>Switch Specifications</h5>
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                <h6>Key Parameters:</h6>
                <table style="width: 100%;">
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Ports</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">5, 8, 16, 24, 48</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Speed</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">10/100/1000 Mbps</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>PoE</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Power over Ethernet</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Backplane</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Internal switching capacity</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>MAC Table Size</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">8K - 32K entries</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #fff3cd; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>Switch vs Hub:</h6>
                    <table style="width: 100%; font-size: 0.8em;">
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 5px;"><b>Switch</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 5px;">Intelligent, directed traffic</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 5px;"><b>Hub</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 5px;">Dumb, broadcasts to all</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 5px;"><b>Collisions</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 5px;">None (full duplex)</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 5px;"><b>Collisions</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 5px;">Many (half duplex)</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #e8f5e8; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>Switch Benefits:</h6>
                    <ul style="font-size: 0.8em;">
                        <li>Reduced collisions</li>
                        <li>Increased security</li>
                        <li>Better performance</li>
                        <li>VLAN support</li>
                        <li>Network management</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>Routers: The Internet Gatekeepers</h3>
<div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
    <div style="background: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
        <h4>ğŸŒ Layer 3 Routing</h4>
        
        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin-top: 10px;">
            <h5>How Routers Work</h5>
            
            <div style="text-align: center; padding: 15px; background: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 5px; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #bbdefb; border-radius: 5px;">LAN<br>192.168.1.0/24</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px;">â†’ Router â†’</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #90caf9; border-radius: 5px;">Internet<br>Public IP</div>
            </div>
            
            <h6>Router Functions:</h6>
            <table style="width: 100%;">
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px; width: 30%;"><b>Path Determination:</b></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Finds best route to destination</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Packet Switching:</b></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Moves packets between interfaces</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>NAT:</b></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Network Address Translation</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Firewall:</b></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">Basic security filtering</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>DHCP Server:</b></td>
                    <td style="padding: 8px;">IP address assignment</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>
        
        <div style="margin-top: 15px; background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <h5>Routing Table Example</h5>
            <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; font-family: monospace;">
Destination      Gateway          Interface      Metric
0.0.0.0/0       203.0.113.1      eth0           10     # Default route
192.168.1.0/24  0.0.0.0          eth1           0      # Local network
10.0.0.0/8       192.168.1.254   eth1           1      # Office network
172.16.0.0/12    192.168.1.253   eth1           5      # Data center
            </pre>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
        <h4>ğŸ”„ NAT - Network Address Translation</h4>
        
        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin-top: 10px;">
            <h5>The Magic of NAT</h5>
            <p>How one public IP serves many private devices:</p>
            
            <div style="margin: 15px 0; padding: 10px; background: #ffebee; border-radius: 5px;">
                <h6>Before NAT (Outbound):</h6>
                <p>Source: 192.168.1.10:54321 â†’ Dest: 8.8.8.8:80</p>
                <p>Router changes to: 203.0.113.5:12345 â†’ 8.8.8.8:80</p>
            </div>
            
            <div style="margin: 15px 0; padding: 10px; background: #f3e5f5; border-radius: 5px;">
                <h6>After NAT (Inbound):</h6>
                <p>Source: 8.8.8.8:80 â†’ Dest: 203.0.113.5:12345</p>
                <p>Router changes to: 8.8.8.8:80 â†’ 192.168.1.10:54321</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div style="margin-top: 15px; background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <h5>Types of NAT</h5>
            <table style="width: 100%;">
