                </pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>Router vs Switch Comparison</h3>
<div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
        <div>
            <h4>ğŸ“Š Feature Comparison</h4>
            
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                <table style="width: 100%;">
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <th style="padding: 10px;">Feature</th>
                        <th style="padding: 10px;">Switch</th>
                        <th style="padding: 10px;">Router</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>OSI Layer</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Layer 2 (Data Link)</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Layer 3 (Network)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Address Used</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">MAC Address</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">IP Address</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Function</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Connect devices in same network</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Connect different networks</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Broadcasts</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Forwards broadcasts</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Blocks broadcasts</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Ports</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Many (24, 48)</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Fewer (4-8)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Speed</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Faster (wire speed)</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Slower (processing overhead)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div>
            <h4>ğŸ”§ Device Selection</h4>
            
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                <h5>When to Use a Switch:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Connecting computers in same office</li>
                    <li>Need more Ethernet ports</li>
                    <li>Creating VLANs within building</li>
                    <li>High-speed local transfers</li>
                    <li>PoE for phones/cameras</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h5 style="margin-top: 15px;">When to Use a Router:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Connecting to Internet</li>
                    <li>Joining different networks</li>
                    <li>Need firewall/NAT</li>
                    <li>VPN connections</li>
                    <li>Traffic filtering</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #e3f2fd; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>Modern Devices:</h6>
                    <p><b>Layer 3 Switches:</b> Switches with routing capabilities</p>
                    <p><b>Wireless Routers:</b> Router + switch + WiFi + firewall</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; background: white; border-radius: 5px;">
        <h5>ğŸ¯ Real-World Example: Home Network</h5>
        
