            <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px;">â†’</div>
            <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 15px; background: #2ecc71; border-radius: 5px;">
                <b>Switch</b><br>
                8-port<br>
                Connects all devices
            </div>
            
            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #f39c12; border-radius: 5px;">Computer</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #9b59b6; color: white; border-radius: 5px;">Printer</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #1abc9c; border-radius: 5px;">NAS</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #34495e; color: white; border-radius: 5px;">Smart TV</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>DNS Introduction</h3>
<div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin: 10px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    <h4>ğŸ“ The Internet's Phone Book</h4>
    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
        <div>
            <h5>What is DNS?</h5>
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                <p><b>Domain Name System (DNS)</b> translates human-friendly domain names into IP addresses that computers use.</p>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #e3f2fd; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>Simple Analogy:</h6>
                    <p><b>Phone Book:</b> Name â†’ Phone Number</p>
                    <p><b>DNS:</b> Domain Name â†’ IP Address</p>
                    <p>google.com â†’ 172.217.164.110</p>
                </div>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 15px;">
                    <h6>Why DNS is Essential:</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Humans remember names better than numbers</li>
                        <li>IP addresses can change (DNS updates)</li>
                        <li>Load balancing across multiple servers</li>
                        <li>Service discovery</li>
                        <li>Email routing</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div>
            <h5>DNS Record Types</h5>
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                <table style="width: 100%;">
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <th style="padding: 8px;">Record</th>
                        <th style="padding: 8px;">Purpose</th>
                        <th style="padding: 8px;">Example</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>A</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">IPv4 Address</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">google.com â†’ 172.217.164.110</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>AAAA</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">IPv6 Address</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">google.com â†’ 2607:f8b0:4004:080a::200e</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>CNAME</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Canonical Name (Alias)</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">www â†’ google.com</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>MX</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Mail Exchange</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">gmail.com â†’ mail servers</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>TXT</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">Text Records</td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">SPF, DKIM for email</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
        <h5>DNS Resolution Process</h5>
        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            
            <div style="text-align: center; padding: 15px;">
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #bbdefb; border-radius: 5px;">Browser<br>"google.com"</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px;">â†’</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #90caf9; border-radius: 5px;">DNS Resolver<br>8.8.8.8</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px;">â†’</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #64b5f6; border-radius: 5px;">Root Server<br>"."</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px;">â†’</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #42a5f5; border-radius: 5px;">TLD Server<br>".com"</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px;">â†’</div>
                <div style="display: inline-block; padding: 10px; background: #2196f3; border-radius: 5px;">Authoritative<br>"google.com"</div>
            </div>
            
            <div style="margin-top: 15px;">
                <h6>Step-by-Step Resolution:</h6>
                <ol>
                    <li>Check browser cache</li>
                    <li>Check OS DNS cache</li>
                    <li>Query DNS resolver (ISP or 8.8.8.8)</li>
                    <li>Resolver queries root servers</li>
                    <li>Root directs to TLD (.com) servers</li>
                    <li>TLD directs to authoritative name servers</li>
                    <li>Authoritative returns IP address</li>
                    <li>Resolver caches result</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

