                icon: "fa-satellite-dish",
                title: "Lab: TraceRoute (tracert) Analysis",
                html: `<h1>Week 6, Day 2: Lab - TraceRoute (tracert) Analysis</h1>
<p>Today we dive deep into network path analysis using TraceRoute, a fundamental tool for understanding how data travels across networks and diagnosing connectivity issues.</p>

<div class="analogy-box">
    <b>Analogy: The Cross-Country Road Trip ğŸš—</b><br/>
    
    TraceRoute: GPS with turn-by-turn directions<br/>
    Hops: Cities along the route<br/>
    RTT: Travel time between cities<br/>
    Timeouts: Road closures or detours<br/>
    AS Numbers: State highway systems<br/>
    TTL: Number of cities you can pass through<br/>
    * * *: "Road under construction"
</div>

<h3>Understanding TraceRoute Fundamentals</h3>
<div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
    <h4>ğŸ¯ How TraceRoute Works</h4>
    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
        <div>
            <h5>The TTL Trick</h5>
            
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; border: 2px solid #3498db;">
                <h6>The Ingenious Method:</h6>
                <p>TraceRoute doesn't ask routers for their locations - it <b>tricks</b> them into revealing themselves!</p>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 15px; background: #e3f2fd; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <h6>Step-by-Step Process:</h6>
                    <ol>
                        <li><b>Packet 1:</b> Send with TTL=1 â†’ First router replies "Time Exceeded"</li>
                        <li><b>Packet 2:</b> Send with TTL=2 â†’ Second router replies</li>
                        <li><b>Packet 3:</b> Send with TTL=3 â†’ Third router replies</li>
                        <li><b>Continue</b> until destination reached or max hops exceeded</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                
                <div style="margin-top: 15px;">
                    <h6>TTL (Time To Live) Explained:</h6>
                    <table style="width: 100%;">
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 8px; width: 30%;"><b>Purpose:</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Prevent infinite routing loops</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Mechanism:</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Decremented by 1 at each router</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>When TTL=0:</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Router discards packet, sends ICMP "Time Exceeded"</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Default Values:</b></td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Windows: 128, Linux: 64, Router: 255</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <h5>ICMP Messages Used</h5>
                <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                    <table style="width: 100%;">
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <th style="padding: 8px;">Type</th>
                            <th style="padding: 8px;">Code</th>
                            <th style="padding: 8px;">Name</th>
                            <th style="padding: 8px;">Purpose in TraceRoute</th>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">11</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">0</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Time Exceeded</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Router response when TTL=0</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">0</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">0</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Echo Reply</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Destination reached (like ping)</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">3</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Various</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Destination Unreachable</td>
                            <td style="padding: 8px;">Path blocked, network unreachable</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div>
            <h5>Quick Reference</h5>
            <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
                <h6>Common Commands:</h6>
                <table style="width: 100%;">
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;"><b>Windows</b></td>
                        <td style="padding: 8px;">tracert</td>
