</div>

<h3>Command Syntax & Options</h3>
<div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
    <div style="background: #e8f5e8; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
        <h4>ğŸ–¥ï¸ Windows Tracert</h4>
        
        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin-top: 10px;">
            <h5>Basic Syntax:</h5>
            <pre style="background: #36454f; color: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
tracert [-d] [-h max_hops] [-j host-list] [-w timeout] target_name

Options:
   -d          Do not resolve addresses to hostnames
   -h max_hops Maximum number of hops to search for target
   -j host-list Loose source route along host-list (IPv4 only)
   -w timeout  Wait timeout milliseconds for each reply
            </pre>
            
            <div style="margin-top: 15px;">
                <h6>Common Examples:</h6>
                <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
# Basic trace to Google
tracert google.com

# Don't resolve hostnames (faster)
tracert -d 8.8.8.8

# Limit to 20 hops maximum
tracert -h 20 facebook.com

# Set timeout to 2 seconds
tracert -w 2000 amazon.com

# Trace to IPv6 address
tracert -6 ipv6.google.com
                </pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div style="background: #ffe6e6; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
        <h4>ğŸ§ Linux/Mac Traceroute</h4>
        
        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin-top: 10px;">
            <h5>Basic Syntax:</h5>
            <pre style="background: #36454f; color: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
traceroute [-I] [-n] [-m max_ttl] [-q nqueries] [-w waittime] host

Options:
   -I          Use ICMP ECHO instead of UDP (like Windows)
   -n          Do not resolve hostnames
   -m max_ttl  Set maximum hops (default: 64)
   -q nqueries Set number of probes per hop (default: 3)
   -w waittime Set time to wait for response (seconds)
   -T          Use TCP SYN (port 80 by default)
   -U          Use UDP (default on most systems)
            </pre>
            
            <div style="margin-top: 15px;">
                <h6>Common Examples:</h6>
                <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
# Basic trace (UDP default)
traceroute google.com

# Use ICMP (like Windows)
traceroute -I google.com

# No DNS resolution
traceroute -n 8.8.8.8

# Limit hops and increase probes
traceroute -m 20 -q 5 facebook.com

# Use TCP on port 443
traceroute -T -p 443 amazon.com

# IPv6 trace
traceroute -6 ipv6.google.com
                </pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

