        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px;">
            
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px;">
                <div>
                    <h5>Common Problems & Solutions:</h5>
                    
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                        <h6>Problem: Timeouts in Middle</h6>
                        <pre style="background: #ffebee; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
Hops 5-7: * * *
Solution:
- Try different protocol (TCP traceroute)
- Check if destination is reachable
- May be normal (some ISPs block)
                        </pre>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div>
                        <h6>Problem: High Latency at Specific Hop</h6>
                        <pre style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
Hop 4: 15ms â†’ Hop 5: 150ms â†’ Hop 6: 155ms
Solution:
- Congestion at that router
- Geographic distance added
- Try at different time of day
                        </pre>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div>
                    <h5>More Problems & Solutions:</h5>
                    
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                        <h6>Problem: Asymmetric Routing</h6>
                        <pre style="background: #e8f5e8; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
Tracert from Aâ†’B different than Bâ†’A
Solution:
- Different ISPs have different routes
- May be intentional for load balancing
- Check if both directions work
                        </pre>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div>
                        <h6>Problem: Route Loops</h6>
                        <pre style="background: #e3f2fd; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;">
Hops: 8, 9, 10, 9, 10, 9, 10...
Solution:
- Routing misconfiguration
- Contact ISP with traceroute results
- May require BGP fix
                        </pre>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div style="margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; background: #fff3cd; border-radius: 5px;">
                <h6>When to Escalate:</h6>
                <ul>
                    <li>Consistent 100% packet loss at specific hop</li>
                    <li>Routing loops that don't resolve</li>
                    <li>Latency > 300ms within same country</li>
                    <li>More than 50% packet loss to destination</li>
                    <li>Private IP addresses in transit path</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

