    <h4>ğŸ›¡ï¸ How HTTPS/TLS Works (Simplified)</h4>
    <ol style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
        <li><b>Client Hello:</b> Browser connects to server on port 443 and sends supported encryption methods</li>
        <li><b>Server Hello:</b> Server responds with chosen encryption method and its SSL certificate</li>
        <li><b>Certificate Verification:</b> Browser verifies certificate with Certificate Authority (CA)</li>
        <li><b>Key Exchange:</b> Client and server establish shared secret key for symmetric encryption</li>
        <li><b>Encrypted Communication:</b> All further communication is encrypted with the shared key</li>
    </ol>
</div>

