<h3>Troubleshooting Common Issues</h3>
<div style="background-color: #fff0e6; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
    <h4>ğŸ”§ Common Problems & Solutions</h4>
    
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background: #e74c3c; color: white;">
            <th style="padding: 8px;">Problem</th>
            <th style="padding: 8px;">Solution</th>
            <th style="padding: 8px;">Command to Check</th>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Port already in use</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Change port or stop conflicting service</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>sudo netstat -tulpn | grep :80</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: white;">
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Permission denied</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Check file permissions and ownership</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>ls -la /var/www/</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Config syntax error</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Test config and check line numbers</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>sudo apache2ctl configtest</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: white;">
            <td style="padding: 8px;">SELinux blocking</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Adjust SELinux context or disable</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>sudo setenforce 0</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Firewall blocking</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Allow ports in firewall</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>sudo ufw allow 80/tcp</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: white;">
            <td style="padding: 8px;">PHP not working</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Install PHP and enable module</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>sudo apt install php libapache2-mod-php</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f8f9fa;">
            <td style="padding: 8px;">.htaccess ignored</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Check AllowOverride setting</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Set <code>AllowOverride All</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: white;">
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Virtual host not working</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;">Check hosts file and server name</td>
            <td style="padding: 8px;"><code>cat /etc/hosts</code></td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    
    <h4>ğŸ“Š Debugging Tools</h4>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px;">
# Check if service is running
sudo systemctl status apache2
sudo systemctl status nginx

# View error logs
sudo tail -f /var/log/apache2/error.log
sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log

# Check open ports
sudo ss -tulpn | grep :80
sudo ss -tulpn | grep :443

# Check configuration
sudo apache2ctl -S  # Show Apache settings
sudo nginx -T       # Show Nginx full config

# Monitor real-time connections
sudo watch -n 1 "netstat -an | grep :80 | wc -l"

# Check disk space
df -h /var/www/

# Check memory usage
free -h
top -b -n 1 | grep -E "(apache|nginx|httpd)"
    </pre>
</div>

<h3>Homework Assignment</h3>
<div style="background-color: #e8f5e8; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
    <b>Build a "Multi-Site Web Server Environment"</b>
    
    <p>Create a complete local development environment with multiple websites served by both Apache and Nginx.</p>
    
    <b>Requirements:</b>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Apache Setup:</b> Configure 3 virtual hosts:
            <ul>
                <li><code>wordpress.local</code> - WordPress site</li>
                <li><code>phpapp.local</code> - Custom PHP application</li>
                <li><code>static.local</code> - Static HTML/CSS/JS site</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><b>Nginx Setup:</b> Configure 3 server blocks:
            <ul>
                <li><code>api.local</code> - Reverse proxy to Node.js app</li>
                <li><code>assets.local</code> - Static file server with caching</li>
                <li><code>loadbalance.local</code> - Load balancer for 2 backend servers</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><b>SSL/TLS:</b> Configure HTTPS for all sites (self-signed certificates)</li>
        <li><b>Security:</b> Implement security headers, rate limiting, and access controls</li>
        <li><b>Monitoring:</b> Set up log rotation and basic monitoring</li>
    </ul>
    
    <b>Deliverables:</b>
    <ol>
        <li>Complete configuration files for all 6 sites</li>
        <li>Screenshot showing all sites working in browser</li>
        <li>Performance comparison report (Apache vs Nginx)</li>
        <li>Troubleshooting guide for common setup issues</li>
        <li>Backup and restore procedures for the configuration</li>
    </ol>
    
    <b>Bonus Challenges:</b>
    <ul>
        <li>Set up PHP-FPM with Nginx</li>
        <li>Implement HTTP/2 or HTTP/3</li>
        <li>Configure automatic SSL with Let's Encrypt (simulated)</li>
        <li>Create a Docker Compose setup for the entire environment</li>
        <li>Build an Ansible playbook to automate the setup</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<h3>Key Learning Points:</h3>
<ol>
    <li><b>Architecture Differences:</b> Process-based (Apache) vs Event-driven (Nginx)</li>
    <li><b>Configuration Management:</b> Virtual hosts vs server blocks</li>
    <li><b>Performance Characteristics:</b> When to use Apache vs Nginx</li>
    <li><b>Security Best Practices:</b> Proper permissions, headers, and access controls</li>
    <li><b>Troubleshooting Skills:</b> Reading logs, testing configs, debugging issues</li>
    <li><b>Real-World Scenarios:</b> Reverse proxy, load balancing, caching setups</li>
</ol>

<div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    <h3>ğŸ’¡ Production Server Best Practices:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Use Separate Users:</b> Run web server as non-root user</li>
        <li><b>Implement Log Rotation:</b> Prevent logs from filling disk</li>
        <li><b>Enable Security Modules:</b> mod_security for Apache, NAXSI for Nginx</li>
        <li><b>Set Resource Limits:</b> Prevent DoS attacks by limiting connections</li>
        <li><b>Regular Updates:</b> Keep server software patched</li>
        <li><b>Monitor Performance:</b> Use tools like Munin, Prometheus, or New Relic</li>
        <li><b>Backup Configurations:</b> Use version control for config files</li>
        <li><b>Test Changes:</b> Always test config changes in staging first</li>
    </ul>
</div>
