                "title": "Connect System Roles to Server Permissions",
                "html": `<h1>Week 9, Day 4: Connecting System Roles to Server Permissions</h1>
<p>Today we bridge the gap between theoretical user roles and practical server permissions. You'll learn how to map business/organizational roles to technical permissions across different server types.</p>

<div class="analogy-box">
    <b>Analogy: Theater Production ğŸ­</b><br/>
    <b>System Roles</b> = Theater roles (Director, Actor, Stagehand, Usher)<br/>
    <b>Server Types</b> = Different theater areas (Stage, Backstage, Box Office, Lobby)<br/>
    <b>Permissions</b> = Access badges for each area<br/>
    <b>Access Control</b> = Security checking badges at each door<br/>
    <b>Audit Trail</b> = Record of who accessed what and when<br/>
    <b>Least Privilege</b> = Only access needed for specific role
</div>

<h3>Understanding System Roles in Organizations</h3>
<div style="background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 10px;">
    <h4>ğŸ‘¥ Common Organizational Roles</h4>
    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">
            <h5>ğŸ“ Educational Institution Roles</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Student:</b> Course access, assignment submission</li>
                <li><b>Teacher/Instructor:</b> Course management, grading</li>
                <li><b>Department Head:</b> Curriculum oversight, teacher management</li>
                <li><b>IT Administrator:</b> System management, user support</li>
                <li><b>Registrar:</b> Enrollment management, records</li>
                <li><b>Guest Lecturer:</b> Temporary teaching access</li>
                <li><b>Researcher:</b> Lab equipment, data access</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">
            <h5>ğŸ¢ Corporate Business Roles</h5>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Employee:</b> Department resources, email</li>
                <li><b>Manager:</b> Team resources, reports</li>
                <li><b>Executive:</b> Strategic data, financials</li>
                <li><b>IT Support:</b> Help desk, basic admin</li>
                <li><b>System Admin:</b> Server management</li>
                <li><b>Developer:</b> Code repositories, test servers</li>
                <li><b>Contractor:</b> Temporary, limited access</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h4>ğŸ”— Role-Permission Mapping Matrix</h4>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0;">
        <tr style="background: #4A90E2; color: white;">
            <th style="padding: 10px; text-align: left;">System Role</th>
