<h3>Key Learning Points:</h3>
<ol>
    <li><b>Threat Diversity:</b> Understanding different attacker motivations and methods</li>
    <li><b>Attack Lifecycle:</b> Recognizing stages of cyber attacks (Kill Chain)</li>
    <li><b>Vulnerability Management:</b> Identifying and prioritizing security weaknesses</li>
    <li><b>Social Engineering:</b> Human psychology as a security vulnerability</li>
    <li><b>Defense in Depth:</b> Multiple layers of security controls</li>
    <li><b>Security Mindset:</b> Thinking like both attacker and defender</li>
</ol>

<div style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 15px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 5px;">
    <h3>ğŸ’¡ Cybersecurity Best Practices:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Assume Breach:</b> Plan for when, not if, you'll be attacked</li>
        <li><b>Least Privilege:</b> Only grant necessary access rights</li>
        <li><b>Defense in Depth:</b> Multiple security layers</li>
        <li><b>Regular Updates:</b> Patch management is critical</li>
        <li><b>Employee Training:</b> Humans are the weakest link</li>
